b'' b'is there such a thing as msg (monosodium glutamate) sensitivity?' b'i saw in the ny times sunday that scientists have testified before' b'an fda advisory panel that complaints about msg sensitivity are' b'superstition. anybody here have experience to the contrary?' b'' b'i know that there is msg sensitivity. when i eat foods with msg i get' b'very thirsty and my hands swell and get a terrible itchy rash. i first' b'experienced this problem when i worked close to chinatown and ate chinese' b"food almost everyday for lunch. now i can't tolerate msg at all. i can" b'notice immediately when i have eaten any. i try to avoid msg completely.' b'' b'interesting fact though is that all three of my children started experiencing' b"the exact same rash on their hands. i couldn't understand why because i" b"don't msg in cooking and we ask for no msg when we do eat chinese (i still" b'love it). after some investigation i knew that oodles of noodles where' b'one of their favorite foods. one of the main ingredients in the flavor' b'packets is msg. now i look at all labels. you would be surprised at' b'places you find msg.' b'' b'' b'/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/' b'adp, networking and communication assessment carderock division' b'branch naval surface warfare' b'code center' b'bethesda, md. dtmb,cd,nswc' b'|' b'(301)227-3379 fax b'/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\/\\\\/\\/' 